On social networks the call was linked to the desire to be able to walk
without fear. To that effect, Andrea
([@AndreaCorner](https://twitter.com/#!/andrecorner/status/187641695045812224))
[es] wrote:

> Exijo! caminar sin miedos ni temores #Remangate

I demand to be able to walk without fear or worry! #Remangate

Although there were some who expressed their disagreement with the act of
rolling it up, like David Prada
([@davidprada)](https://twitter.com/#!/davidprada/status/187646271870345216)
[es]:

> Remangarse el pantalón le es tan útil a las víctimas de minas como una foto
> de aire lo es para alguien q se esta ahogando. #Remangate

Rolling up your pant leg is about as useful to the victims as a picture of air
is to someone who is drowning. #Remangate

Alejandra Alzate
([@aleja_alzate](https://twitter.com/#!/Aleja_Alzate/status/187641709847515136))
[es] wrote that he was skeptical about the day:

> Sinceramente no pensé que tanta gente fuera a demostrar admiración,apoyo y
> respeto por las victimas de las minas antipersona [~~#~~
> **REMANGATE**](https://twitter.com/#%21/search/%23REMANGATE "#REMANGATE")
> [~~#~~ **FF**](https://twitter.com/#%21/search/%23FF "#FF")

I honestly didn't think that so many people would show such admiration,
support, and respect for victims of antipersonnel mines [~~#~~
**REMANGATE**](https://twitter.com/#%21/search/%23REMANGATE "#REMANGATE")
[~~#~~ **FF**](https://twitter.com/#%21/search/%23FF "#FF")

While still others called for coexistence and tolerance. Lau G. Osorio
([@Deathlovenight](https://twitter.com/#!/DeathNightLove/status/187645654103891970))
posted:

> Pero ustedes todo lo pelean ¿quieren remangarse? Haganlo. ¿ No quieren
> remangarse? No lo hagan y dejen de joder. #remángate

To all of you fighting it: you want to roll it up? Go ahead. You don't want
to? Well then don't and stop bothering. #remángate

On the [official global campaign website](http://lendyourleg.org) you can find
photos and videos about the event. What is more, the [United Nations Mine
Action Service](http://mineaction.org) invited netizens to post photos of
themselves “lending their leg”.
[@MineAction](https://twitter.com/#!/mineaction/status/187668556907937792)
asked:

> Take photos of you “lending your leg” & add them to the [~~#~~
> **lendyourleg**](https://twitter.com/#%21/search/%23lendyourleg
> "#lendyourleg") for a [~~#~~
> **landmine**](https://twitter.com/#%21/search/%23landmine "#landmine") free
> world [~~@~~ **Flickr**](https://twitter.com/#%21/Flickr) group!
